// What is Parcel?
// Parcel is a bundler that takes multiple JavaScript files and combines them into a single file, which can improve performance by reducing the number of requests made to the server.
// install parcel : npm install --save-dev parcel (it will install parcel in devDependencies not in dependencies)

// How to use parcel?
// parcel only needs an entry point, which is the main file of your application.
// example : your main file is index,js
// how can run parcel : npx parcel index.html

// why the need of installing npm install @parcel/source-map?
// npm install @parcel/source-map
// bcz it is used to generate source maps, which are files that show the original source code of a file that has been transformed by Parcel.
